15 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
16 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law not to be
17 codified in the Oklahoma Statutes reads as follows:
18 This act shall be known and may be cited as the "State Parks
19 Emergency Maintenance Act".
20 SECTION 2. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
21 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 2254.3A of Title 74, unless
22 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
23 Beginning December 31, 2025, and no later than December 31 each
24 year thereafter, the Oklahoma Tourism and Recreation Department
Req. No. 10755 Page 1

1 shal l submit in written or electronic format to the Governor, the
2 Speaker of the Oklahoma House of Representatives, the President Pro
3 Tempore of the Oklahoma State Senate, the Appropriations and Budget
4 Chair of the Oklahoma House of Representatives, and the
5 Appropriations Chair of the Oklahoma State Senate an annual report
6 on the maintenance, infrastructure, and construction needs of the
7 State Parks System overseen by the Oklahoma Tourism and Recreation
8 Department. The annual report shall be known and may be cited as
9 the "Eight-Year State Parks Emergency Maintenance Plan", and shall
10 include:
11 1. Maintenance, infrastructure, and construction projects
12 listed in order of priority and critical need;
13 2. Cost estimates for each specific project listed in
14 paragraph 1 of this subsection;
15 3. Completion timeline for each specific project listed in
16 paragraph 1 of this subsection; and
17 4. A summary of the status of projects previously funded and
18 currently being funded pursuant to the provisions of the State Parks
19 Emergency Maintenance Act.
20 SECTION 3. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
21 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 2254.3B of Title 74, unless
22 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
23 There is hereby created in the State Treasury a revolving fund
24 for the Oklahoma Tourism and Recreation Department to be designated
Req. No. 10755 Page 2

1 the "State Parks Emergency Maintenance Revolving Fund". The fund
2 shall be a continuing fund, not subject to fiscal year limitations,
3 and shall consist of all monies received by the Oklahoma Tourism and
4 Recreation Department eligible under law and directed for deposit to
5 such fund. All monies accruing to the credit of said fund are
6 hereby appropriated and may be budgeted and expended by the Oklahoma
7 Tourism and Recreation Department in amounts as authorized by the
8 Oklahoma Legislature, for the purpose of implementing the
9 Department's Eight-Year State Parks Emergency Maintenance Plan, as
10 described in Section 2 of this act; provided, that in no event shall
11 an amount greater than twenty percent (20%) of the annual amount
12 accruing to the fund shall be used for funding operational expenses
13 of the Department in any given state fiscal year. Expenditures from
14 said fund shall be made upon warrants issued by the State Treasurer
15 against claims filed as prescribed by law with the Director of the
16 Office of Management and Enterprise Services for approval and
17 payment.
18 SECTION 4. This act shall become effective July 1, 2025.
19 SECTION 5. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
20 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
21 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
22 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
